        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "In ZF 1.9 RC there is an attempt to fix the PHP 5.3.0 bug involving MYSQL_ATTR_INIT_COMMAND not being defined.\nThe fix replaces the constant with the value 1002.\nAs commented in the PHP bug reports, this fix does not work on a Windows x64\/MySQL 5.1.36\/PHP 5.3.0 0 just an example.\nThere is no longer a parse error but the effect does not occur.\n\nThe fix should attempt to run a SET NAMES command when first connecting to the database.\nThis or wait for the PHP fix :)\n\nThanks!"
        },
