        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/34867",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=vipsoft",
                        "name": "vipsoft",
                        "displayName": "Anthon Pang, VIP Software Technologies Inc.",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "For reference: http:\/\/bugs.php.net\/bug.php?id=47224\n\nPropose that Pdp\/Mysql.php follow the Pgsql.php implementation --  i.e., exec('SET NAMES'...) -- instead of lazy init.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=vipsoft",
                        "name": "vipsoft",
                        "displayName": "Anthon Pang, VIP Software Technologies Inc.",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-09-24T09:33:56.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-09-24T09:33:56.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/34883",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=costinb",
                        "name": "costinb",
                        "displayName": "Costin Bereveanu",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I wouldn't advise that. The lazy init is a powerful feature. The implementation may be simpler (execute set names right after the connection is actually created (when needed))\nAnyway, I believe they will address this issue in the PHP extension too (hopefully)",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=costinb",
                        "name": "costinb",
                        "displayName": "Costin Bereveanu",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-09-24T17:19:05.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-09-24T17:19:05.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/38037",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ramon",
                        "name": "ramon",
                        "displayName": "Ramon Henrique Ornelas",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This problem occurs in pdo_mysql in SO(windows).\r\n\r\nthe mysqli adapter without problems since it makes use of the function [mysqli_set_charset|http:\/\/br.php.net\/manual\/en\/mysqli.set-charset.php].\r\n\r\nNeeds only set charset in configuration of the adapter.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ramon",
                        "name": "ramon",
                        "displayName": "Ramon Henrique Ornelas",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-01-25T20:12:58.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-01-25T20:12:58.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/43217",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ralph",
                        "name": "ralph",
                        "displayName": "Ralph Schindler",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This appears to be fixed in PHP 5.3.1+, if this is not the case, please reopen this issue.\r\n\r\nThanks,\r\nRalph",
